for the second Olympics in a row, having only turned 16 earlier this month.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2091, \"end\": 2098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999997467057, \"rank\": 2.532245441506474e-10, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are plenty of other young athletes representing their countries.\", \"from\": 2198, \"to\": 2268, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hezly Rivera, who has just turned 16, will represent Team USA in the gymnastics, while another 16-year-old, Quincy Wilson, has become the youngest athlete in US track and field history as he heads to Paris in the 4x400m relay squad.\", \"from\": 2269, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2275, \"end\": 2281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariano_Rivera\", \"score\": 0.9999847138630781, \"rank\": 1.5230560984648545e-05, \"text\": \"Rivera\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariano_Rivera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariano_Rivera\"}, {\"begin\": 2322, \"end\": 2330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.8910306071929942, \"rank\": 0.12229590204554487, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2377, \"end\": 2383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.9993510739065322, \"rank\": 0.00047714706706666546, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 2384, \"