from\": 2596, \"to\": 2691, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Hanna may not actually compete in Paris, as she is currently an AP athlete (known as a non-competing athlete) and is on standby in case of injury, for example.\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2702, \"end\": 2707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanna_Marin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.755508402287492e-15, \"text\": \"Hanna\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanna_Marin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hanna_Marin\"}, {\"begin\": 2736, \"end\": 2741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999769986518, \"rank\": 2.3001337731163678e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2766, \"end\": 2768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9999948648826347, \"rank\": 5.039921129785878e-06, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her Olympic debut came in Atlanta in 1996, though she has never won a medal.\", \"from\": 2862, \"to\": 2938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2888, \"end\": 2895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9999999984265742, \"rank\": 1.0444924320807423e-09, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The oldest athlete set to definitely compete will also be in equestrian - Juan Antonio Jimenez Cobo of Spain, who is 65.\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 3060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3043, \"end\": 3048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.778548012239691, \"rank\": 0.2843822120454181, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jimenez Cobo will be taking part in his third Olympic Games, having debuted in Sydney in 2000.\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3140, \"end\": 3146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9999998856974409, \"rank\": 9.49796343717601e-08, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He took home the silver medal in team dressage in Athens in 2004 but has not been to an Olympics since then.\", \"from\": 3156, \"to\": 3264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3206, \"end\": 3212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.808811260710902e-16, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From a Team GB perspective, 57-year-old Carl Hester is the oldest competitor and he will make history by equalling fellow equestrian legend Nick Skelton's record of seven Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 3266, \"to\": 3451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3273, \"end\": 3280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999997467057, \"rank\": 2.532245441506474e-10, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 3306, \"end\": 3317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carl_Hester\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carl Hester\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"]